headline: SkyWest’s New Airline Contracts Support E175 Growth And Valuation Upside
summary: SkyWest, Inc. (NasdaqGS:SKYW) has secured multi year contract extensions with United Airlines and Delta Air Lines for its Embraer E175 fleet. The company is expanding its partnership with Embraer and setting out growth plans that run through 2028. These agreements increase visibility on aircraft deployment and future revenue for SkyWest's regional operations. headline: Trump Threatens to Decertify, Levy Tariff on Canadian Planes
summary: Trump said Canada had “wrongfully, illegally, and steadfastly refused to certify the Gulfstream 500, 600, 700, and 800 Jets,” in a social media post Thursday.  In response, he said the US would decertify “Bombardier Global Expresses, and all Aircraft made in Canada, until such time as Gulfstream, a Great American Company, is fully certified.”
